# MAC-to-device-name mapping for auto-detection.
#
# When DEVICE is not set on the command line, Make queries the connected
# board's MAC address via `espflash board-info` and looks it up here.
#
# Format: MAC_ADDRESS  device-name
# The device-name must match a file in this directory: <device-name>.mk
#
# Tip: run `espflash board-info` to find the MAC of the connected board,
# then add a line here and create the corresponding .mk file.

# aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:f0  myboard-kitchen
# aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:f1  myboard-garage
